The significant gain over official baselines (+3.8% AUROC) is attributed to the dual-stream modeling of temporal dynamics and medical semantics. Unlike SSSD or CSDI, which focus primarily on the stochastic reconstruction of missing values, \textbf{S-DGI} utilizes UMLS priors to stabilize the representation in high-dimensional sparse scenarios.